<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     HEAD-TO-HEAD COMPARISON
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section section-alt" id="comparison">
  <div class="eyebrow eyebrow-o">Head-to-Head</div>
  <h2 class="sh">17-Dimension Comparison</h2>
  <p class="ss">Every structural difference between the two programs — with a verdict on which platform wins each dimension and why.</p>

  <div class="comp-wrap">
    <table class="comp-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th class="th-dim">Dimension</th>
          <th class="th-kast">KAST</th>
          <th class="th-rdp">Redotpay</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td>Commission model</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Flat spend bonus + % of card fee + % of transactions <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td class="cell-r">% of card fee + % of transactions only</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Transaction commission rate</td>
          <td class="cell-k"><strong>0.10–0.35%</strong> recurring, lifetime <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td><strong>0.05% (LV1) → 0.10% (LV2)</strong> — scales by tier; LV3 undisclosed</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Transaction settlement speed</td>
          <td class="cell-k"><strong>Instant</strong> — no stated lag <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td><strong>30 days</strong> monthly settlement <span class="badge-warn">Key weakness</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Card activation payout</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Instant USDC</td>
          <td class="cell-r">Instant USDT <span class="badge-tie">Tie</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Tier 2 earnings</td>
          <td>+10% of referral's total earnings</td>
          <td>10% of referral's commission earnings <span class="badge-tie">Effectively equal</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Payout currency</td>
          <td>USDC only</td>
          <td class="cell-r">USDT, BTC, ETH, bank transfer <span class="badge-r">Redotpay wins</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Tier thresholds</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Fully published: 5 / 50 / 100 / 500 <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td class="cell-r">Published: LV1 (0–9) / LV2 (10–29) / LV3 (30+) — LV3 top rates undisclosed</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Commission rates transparency</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Full tier table publicly available <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td>LV1 &amp; LV2 rates confirmed public; LV3 ceiling and Angels terms undisclosed <span class="badge-warn">Partial opacity</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Token / points upside</td>
          <td class="cell-k">KAST Points → Q2 2026 TGE (dual-stack incentive) <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td>No equivalent token or points program</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Competitive leaderboard</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Live leaderboard — up to $1,000 USDC/day in prizes <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td>No published leaderboard or competitive mechanic</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Active promotions</td>
          <td class="cell-k">2× commission (indefinite, no cap) <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td>No active promo published</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Physical card fee (user side)</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Free entry-level card available <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td><strong>$100</strong> physical card — highest in category <span class="badge-warn">Highest barrier</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Distribution programs</td>
          <td>1 program (Affiliate)</td>
          <td class="cell-r">4 parallel programs (Referral + KOL + Affiliate + Angels) <span class="badge-r">Redotpay wins</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Geographic reach</td>
          <td>Not publicly stated</td>
          <td class="cell-r">160+ countries <span class="badge-r">Redotpay wins</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Open registration</td>
          <td class="cell-k">Yes — no KYC required to join affiliate program <span class="badge-k">KAST wins</span></td>
          <td>KYC-verified account required before activation</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>Elite tier mechanics</td>
          <td>VIP (invite-only, criteria not published)</td>
          <td class="cell-r">Redot Angels — invite-only + event access + co-marketing <span class="badge-r">Redotpay wins</span></td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td>New user sign-up bonus</td>
          <td>Not published as a standard feature</td>
          <td class="cell-r">$5 USD for new users activating via referral code <span class="badge-r">Redotpay wins</span></td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="div">

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     DOCUMENTED WEAKNESSES
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section" id="weaknesses">
  <div class="eyebrow eyebrow-o">Documented Weaknesses</div>
  <h2 class="sh">Known gaps in both programs</h2>
  <p class="ss">Each weakness is a specific, addressable structural failure — not speculation. These are sourced from public documentation, affiliate community reviews, and Trustpilot data as of March 2026.</p>

  <div class="weak-grid">
    <!-- KAST weaknesses -->
    <div class="weak-col">
      <div class="weak-col-header wch-k">
        <div class="wch-badge wbg-k">K</div>
        <div>
          <div class="wch-name">KAST — Affiliate Program Gaps</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-k">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Medium</span>
        <div class="weak-title">No dormant affiliate reactivation mechanic</div>
        <div class="weak-body">No published mechanism for re-engaging affiliates who go silent (15+ days of no referral activity). This is the most common point of leakage in all affiliate programs — neither KAST nor Redotpay has addressed it with any documented system.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-k">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Medium</span>
        <div class="weak-title">VIP tier criteria entirely opaque</div>
        <div class="weak-body">The top tier is invite-only with no public criteria, no application process, and no stated benefits. Affiliates cannot see or work toward elite status — reducing the motivational power of the top tier as a goal.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-k">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Medium</span>
        <div class="weak-title">KAST Points value tied to TGE execution risk</div>
        <div class="weak-body">The dual-stack incentive depends on successful Q2 2026 TGE delivery. Points notional value ($0.10 FDV) is not locked. If TGE is delayed or underperforms, the token upside component of KAST's affiliate pitch is significantly weakened.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-k">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Low</span>
        <div class="weak-title">No creator-native tooling or affiliate community</div>
        <div class="weak-body">No affiliate-specific creative assets, co-branded landing pages, UTM builders, or embeddable widgets. Affiliates are given a link and left to figure it out. No community forum, playbook, or performance coaching beyond the dashboard number.</div>
      </div>
    </div>

    <!-- Redotpay weaknesses -->
    <div class="weak-col">
      <div class="weak-col-header wch-r">
        <div class="wch-badge wbg-r">R</div>
        <div>
          <div class="wch-name">Redotpay — Affiliate Program Gaps</div>
        </div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-r weak-card-crit">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-high">Critical</span>
        <div class="weak-title">30-day transaction commission lag</div>
        <div class="weak-body">Transaction commissions settle monthly. For affiliates in high-time-preference markets (SEA, LATAM, Africa), a 30-day cash flow wait is a dealbreaker. Confirmed as the primary reason KAST out-recruits Redotpay on KOL quality despite 1/6th the user base. Cashi should publish a weekly settlement as a direct counter-positioning claim.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-r">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Medium</span>
        <div class="weak-title">LV3 top-end rates and Redot Angels terms not published</div>
        <div class="weak-body">LV1 and LV2 rates are now publicly confirmed. However, LV3 maximum commission rates and all Redot Angels terms remain undisclosed and individually negotiated. Affiliates cannot see the ceiling they're working toward — a residual trust friction a fully-transparent rate card still exploits.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-r weak-card-crit">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-high">Critical</span>
        <div class="weak-title">$100 physical card fee — highest in category</div>
        <div class="weak-body">Redotpay charges $100 for physical card issuance, compared to a free entry card at KAST. A significant portion of Redotpay's 6M user base has no physical card as a result. This is simultaneously a revenue model (high per-activation payouts) and an acquisition suppressor (highest barrier in the category).</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-r">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-high">High</span>
        <div class="weak-title">3.8/5 Trustpilot — service quality failures at scale</div>
        <div class="weak-body">Frozen funds, 1–3 day KYC delays (vs. KAST's 2–3 minutes), and unresponsive support documented across reviews. 5+ senior departures (no active CFO as of early 2026). China-ties sensitivity ahead of a US IPO. At 6M users, these failures compound faster than they can be fixed through review-driven organic acquisition channels.</div>
      </div>
      <div class="weak-card weak-card-r">
        <span class="weak-sev sev-med">Medium</span>
        <div class="weak-title">No gamification, leaderboard, or competitive mechanic</div>
        <div class="weak-body">No points, no leaderboard prizes, no competitive ranking system. Compared to KAST's daily USDC leaderboard prizes and points-to-TGE mechanic, Redotpay's affiliate program is purely transactional with no engagement or retention layer beyond the commission itself.</div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="div">

<!-- ═══════════════════════════════════════
     POSITIONING VERDICT
════════════════════════════════════════ -->
<div class="section section-alt" id="positioning">
  <div class="eyebrow eyebrow-o">Positioning Verdict</div>
  <h2 class="sh">Where each platform has staked its claim — and where Cashi enters</h2>
  <p class="ss">Both programs have claimed distinct poles. The most valuable position in the category is the one neither has taken.</p>

  <div class="verdict-grid">
    <div class="verdict-card vc-k">
      <div class="verdict-label vl-k">KAST owns</div>
      <div class="verdict-title">Aspirational / Premium</div>
      <div class="verdict-body">Metal cards, Luxe tier, concierge branding, elite affiliate bonuses. Instant USDC + TGE dual-stack attracts quality KOLs. Revenue per user ~$65 — 2–3× higher than Redotpay despite 1/6th the scale. Wins on unit economics and affiliate quality.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="verdict-card vc-r">
      <div class="verdict-label vl-r">Redotpay owns</div>
      <div class="verdict-title">Institutional / Scale</div>
      <div class="verdict-body">B2B-first, 160+ countries, four parallel distribution programs, corridor strategy (BRL/MXN/NGN). 6M users, unicorn in 29 months. Wins on volume and geographic breadth. Revenue per user ~$25 — lower unit economics, higher absolute scale.</div>
    </div>
    <div class="verdict-card vc-cashi">
      <div class="verdict-label vl-o">Cashi's open lane</div>
      <div class="verdict-title">Affiliate-First, Creator-Native, Everyday</div>
      <div class="verdict-body">Neither platform has claimed the transparent, community-first positioning. The mass-market everyday neobank for crypto — approachable, fast, rewarding from day one. Affiliates treated as partners, not a distribution channel.</div>
      <div class="verdict-quote">"The affiliate program built for people who take this seriously." — Transparent economics, weekly payouts, real tooling, real community, micro-win feedback loops, and a clear ladder from first-time micro-affiliate to elite Black-tier partner.</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>

<hr class="div">

